  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Water, Sanitation and Hygiene Humanitarian Assistance to Affected Populations in Mafa and Kala Balge LGAs, Borno state, North Eastern Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tdh plans to implement a 8-month project which focusses on the provision of life-saving WASH support to vulnerable populations most in need in Mafa and Kala Balge local governorates. Tdh plans to support a total of 52,500 individuals. This project will build upon Tdh&#x2019;s experience providing WASH services in the targeted areas and contribute to the overall objective of the Nigeria Humanitarian response strategy plan to Save lives by providing timely and integrated multi-sector assistance and protection interventions to the most vulnerable, IDPs, returnees and host communities.The project will strive to increase and improve access to safe and equitable water, sanitation and hygiene thereby contribute to save lives, improve health, safety and dignity of the affected population. The action will also boost the cholera outbreak preparedness in the targeted areas. The first and second outputs of the proposed project will focus on improving the standards of water and sanitation facilities through installation of emergency water and sanitation infrastructures to new and emerging caseloads, and by ensuring the operation and maintenances of water and sanitation infrastructures  (installation of water points, repair and or upgrade of water points, chlorination of water points, latrines and bathing facilities repairs, desludging and decommissioning of sanitation infrastructures). The Third output focuses on hygiene practices improvement through community awareness raising sessions and distribution of hygiene kits to practice all or some of promoted messages.</narrative>
  </description>
